### 6b — setState-in-effect on line 239

**Find the `useEffect`** around line 237–242 that calls `setCloudStatus` or similar state setter synchronously:
```ts
useEffect(() => {
  setCloudStatus('unsaved')   // ← called synchronously without a guard
  ...
}, [state, user?.id, lastSyncedState])
```

**Look at the full effect.** It already has if/else conditions inside. Make sure every `setState` call is inside an `if` branch, not at the top level of the effect callback. If you see a setter called unconditionally, wrap it:
```ts
useEffect(() => {
  if (!user) {
    setCloudStatus('local')  // already conditional — fine
    return
  }
  // ... rest of the logic
}, [state, user?.id, lastSyncedState])
```

The ESLint rule fires when a setter is reachable without any condition. Read the effect body and make sure every `set*` call has a condition before it.

