## Commit style

Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):

| Prefix | When to use |
|--------|-------------|
| `feat:` | New feature |
| `fix:` | Bug fix |
| `test:` | Adding or updating tests |
| `refactor:` | Code change that is not a fix or feature |
| `docs:` | Documentation only |
| `ci:` | CI/CD config |
| `clean:` | Removing files or dead code |
| `chore:` | Tooling, dependencies |

## Before opening a PR

- [ ] `npm run lint` — 0 errors
- [ ] `npm test` — all tests pass
- [ ] `npm run build` — clean build
- [ ] No new `console.log` statements in src/

## Project structure

```
src/
  components/ats/     ATS checker UI (split into focused components)
  components/form/    Form inputs per resume section
  components/templates/ The 10 resume templates
  context/            App state (ResumeDataContext + ResumeSyncContext)
  hooks/              Custom React hooks
  pages/              Route-level page components
  utils/              ATS scoring engine (pure TS, no React)
  types/              TypeScript interfaces
```

## Architecture notes

- **Local-first:** All resume data lives in `localStorage`. Supabase sync is optional.
- **ATS engine:** Pure TypeScript in `src/utils/ats*.ts`. No React. Fully testable.
- **No `any` types:** Use `unknown` + type guards instead.
- **No ref-during-render:** Always update `ref.current` inside `useEffect`, never at component top level.
```

